        "subject": "LU-2808 osp: tolerate truncates on striped objects",
        "message": "LU-2808 osp: tolerate truncates on striped objects\n\nIf a client lacks lsm for a file then it may send setattr from\ntruncate to the MDS even if the file already has stripes.  Tolerate\nthis in osp_declare_attr_set()/osp_object_assign_fid() by not LBUGing.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I088e2278cc9ac1c9c029fa854b6efd6bdc933a89\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
